    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Offering an investment-grade 1994 Mazda RX-7 (FD3S) in pristine condition. This chassis remains a benchmark for 50/50 weight distribution and lightweight engineering. The 13B-REW power plant has been meticulously maintained, featuring a healthy sequential twin-turbocharger setup with no boost leaks or actuator hesitation. A recent compression test yielded exceptional, uniform results across all rotor faces. The drivetrain is anchored by a crisp five-speed manual gearbox and a Torsen limited-slip differential, ensuring linear power delivery. The suspension geometry is factory-spec but enhanced with refreshed bushings and adjustable dampers for optimal damping rebound. The exterior retains its original deep luster, while the cockpit is free of the typical dash-plastic delamination. This is a turn-key example for the discerning rotary enthusiast seeking mechanical perfection.",
